      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "The term \"spooky action at a distance\" was coined by Albert Einstein, who believed it was an \"unholy specter\" that threatened the principle of locality in physics. This term refers to the seemingly instantaneous correlation between entangled particles, which happens even if they're separated by large distances, violating the idea that information can only travel at a finite speed. What Einstein thought was \"spooky\" was that the connection between these particles allowed for information to be transmitted faster-than-light.",
